The paper deals with increasing the capacity of discrete memoryless channels (DMC) with high input cardinality, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and communication theory (cs.COMM). The paper also discusses different design criteria for the input subset, which could fall under the category of signal processing (cs.SI). The algorithm developed to solve the problem is based on maximization, which could be related to optimization (cs.DS). Finally, the paper applies the method to a mono-bit transceiver MIMO system, which could be related to networking (cs.NI).
